## Step 2 ‚Äî Define the documentation standard (single source of truth)

Write the conventions all routes must follow (add as a short section to the
`deno-backend` skill's `references/layer-patterns.md` *or* a new
`references/openapi-docs.md`, and link it). Standard:

1. **`summary`** ‚Äî imperative, ‚â§ ~60 chars ("Create note", "List document folders").
   Every operation MUST have one.
2. **`description`** ‚Äî Markdown, required for every operation. Template:
   ```
   <One/two sentence purpose.>

   **Behavior:** <what it does, side effects, async/queued work>
   **Auth:** <cookie session | API key | super-admin | internal tool | public>
   **Permissions:** <permission group / ownership checks, if any>
   **Notes:** <tenant scoping, rate limits, idempotency, pagination, etc.>
   ```
3. **`operationId`** ‚Äî required, stable, `camelCase`, unique across the spec
   (e.g. `notesList`, `notesCreate`, `documentFoldersBulkMove`). Establish a
   naming scheme: `<featureCamel><Action>`.
4. **`tags`** ‚Äî reuse `OpenAPITags`; add a **`description`** for every tag in
   `openApiTagsSpec` (see Step 3).
5. **`deprecated`** ‚Äî set on any endpoint slated for removal; mention replacement in
   `description`.
6. **`security` override** ‚Äî public endpoints get `security: []`; internal/admin get
   the right scheme so the "lock" icon is accurate.
7. **Examples** ‚Äî
   - Every request body schema and key response schema carries at least one realistic
     `example` (prefer registered components with field-level examples in `models/`).
   - **Multi-shape inputs**: model as `z.discriminatedUnion`/`z.union` and attach a
     **named `examples` map** (one per variant, each with `summary` + `value`).
8. **Error responses** ‚Äî keep using the shared `httpResponse*` blocks; ensure each
   operation lists the errors it can actually return (don't over- or under-declare).

Also fix the **base spec** (`open-api-base.ts`): real `info.title`,
`info.description` (overview + auth model + base URL + environments), `contact`,
`license`, and optionally top-level `externalDocs` pointing at the README.

