## Step 6 ‚Äî Verification

Per feature and again at the end:

```sh
deno fmt
deno lint
deno check main.ts
deno run --allow-read .agents/skills/deno-backend/scripts/verify_deps.ts
```

Spec/render checks:

1. Start the dev server and fetch `GET /docs`; assert it is valid JSON and that the
   newly documented operations carry `summary`, `description`, `operationId`, and
   `tags`. (A small script can iterate `spec.paths` and assert no operation is missing
   these fields ‚Äî turn this into a CI gate.)
2. Open `GET /openapi` (Scalar) and visually confirm: tag descriptions show, examples
   render, `oneOf` variants + named examples are selectable, security locks are correct.
3. Confirm prod-mode `/docs` (public-only app) still builds and only exposes intended
   public endpoints.
4. Optionally run the spec through an OpenAPI validator (e.g. Scalar/Redocly CLI) for
   3.0.0 conformance.

**Proposed CI gate (new):** a `scripts/check-openapi-docs.ts` that loads the document
via `app.getOpenAPIDocument(openApiBaseSpec)` and fails if any operation lacks
`summary`/`description`/`operationId`, or if any used tag lacks a description. This
prevents regression after the pass.

