## Risks / Notes

- **Behavioral accuracy:** descriptions must come from reading handlers/services, not
  path guessing ‚Äî that is the point of Step 1.
- **Component name collisions:** `.openapi("Name")` registers global components; keep
  names unique per feature (`NoteCreateRequest`, `DocumentCreateRequest`, ‚Ä¶).
- **Route ordering:** documentation edits must not touch the carefully ordered route
  registration in `index.ts`/`main.ts` (specific-before-generic). Docs are metadata only.
- **Prod vs dev exposure:** verify nothing intended to stay private becomes visible via
  `/docs` after edits.
- **Scope:** large pass (262 operations). Land it incrementally per feature behind the
  CI gate rather than one giant change.
